**Worst coverage gap**: `common/src/operator.rs` — 6 `FlatInfo` variants have no round-trip tests. Since the discriminant is the `SubEvent` wire value in the Havoc protocol, a mis-matched constant would silently corrupt the operator event stream with no compile-time or test-time signal.

**Trend**: Coverage is strong and improving. The codebase has excellent unit test depth in `agents.rs`, `auth.rs`, and `api.rs`. The remaining gaps are concentrated in protocol serialization edge cases and one routing integration test — not in core business logic.
